      "description": "Offered is an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in pristine, concours-ready condition. This example features the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six power plant, utilizing six individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing for a surgical throttle response. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. Critical preventative maintenance has been executed to the highest standard, including a comprehensive subframe reinforcement, rod bearing replacement, and a full VANOS bulletproofing. The suspension geometry is sharpened by a Bilstein PSS10 coilover system, providing exceptional damping control without compromising chassis rigidity. The exterior retains its factory depth and clarity, free of rock chips or swirl marks, while the interior leather shows no bolster wear or UV degradation. A turn-key specimen for the technical purist.",
